@node Install "Installation"

JISConvert requires no installation.  JISConvert  may  be  moved  to  other
disk volumes or directories by dragging it's  icon  to  the  new  location.
See  the  Amiga  Users  Guide that was included with the computer for  more
information.

@endnode

@node Reference "Reference Guide"

                        JISConvert Reference Guide

===========================================================================

Click on one of the gadgets below for more specific information.

    @{ " Input File Selection               " link Input     }
    @{ " Output File Selection              " link Output    }
    @{ " Output File Format Selection       " link Format    }
    @{ " Program Options                    " link Options }

@endnode

@node Input "Input File"

The "Input File"  gadget  is  used  to  select  the  file  that  is  to  be
converted.

@endnode

@node Output "Output File"

The "Output File" gadget is used to select the file to be created with  the
converted output.  The output file can not be the same file  as  the  input
file.

@endnode

@node Format "Output File Format"

This is the format the input  file  will  be  converted  to.   The  various
formats supported are EUC, New JIS, Old JIS, Nec JIS and Shift JIS.

@endnode

@node Options "Program Options"

There are two conversion options:

     Convert half size katakana to full size - This converts half width
     Katakana characters to their full width equivalents.

     Repair files with ESC chars stripped -  This  option  attempts  to
     put  the  missing  ESC  characters  back  into  a  damaged   file.
     However, this option can cause mangled output if it is used  on  a
     file that does not have the ESC codes stripped off.

@endnode

@node Requirements "Program Requirements"

JISConvert will run on all Amiga models that have  at  minimum  of  60K  of
free memory.  JISConvert requires AmigaDos 2.04 or newer to operate.

@endnode
